cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Recommenders as Control Surfaces for LLM Agents: Adversarial Feed Injection, Model Regimes, and Simple Defenses"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Rana"
    given-names: "Muhammad Usman"
    email: "usmanashrafrana@gmail.com"
abstract: >
  We study whether the choice of feed-ranking algorithm consumed by an LLM
  agent during a multi-turn exposure phase can steer the agent's downstream
  decisions, holding model, persona, topic, and final prompt fixed. Across
  2,465 decision rollouts and four modern open instruct LLMs from three labs,
  we find that adversarial post injection produces statistically significant
  decision shifts in two of four model families (Llama 3.2-3B, Gemma 4-e4b),
  replicates with a generator-swap, follows a dose-response curve, is
  directionally asymmetric to the model's default, and yields to two simple
  feed-level defenses. We further document a methodological warning:
  standard random-CV activation probing overstates "hidden mechanism" claims
  in multi-turn agent settings.
keywords:
  - large language models
  - agentic AI
  - adversarial attacks
  - prompt injection
  - recommender systems
  - AI safety
  - feed manipulation
license: MIT
